      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 62-year-old patient presents with persistent abdominal pain and jaundice. On further evaluation, a cholangiogram reveals the presence of cholangiocarcinoma. What is the most likely cause of this patient&#39;s condition?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q3225353",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
